\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 friend's arm.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Look!" he whispered.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Far \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to the south glowed a solitary point of light, too low
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 in the heavens to be a star. It was a brilliant white, tinged
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 with violet, and as the boys watched it began to climb the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 spectrum of intensity, until the eye could no longer bear to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 look upon it. Then \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 it exploded\hich\f39 \emdash \loch\f39 and it seemed as if lightning
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had struck below the rim of the world. For an instant the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mountains, and the great land -they guarded, were etched
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 with Ere against the darkness of the night. Ages later came
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the echo of a mighty explosion, and in \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the forest below a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 63
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 64 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 sudden wind stirred among the trees. It died away swiftly,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and one by one the routed stars crept back into the sky.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 For the Erst time in his life, Alvin knew that fear of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 unknown that had been the curse of ancient man. It was a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 feeling so strange that for a while he could not even give it a
