\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had tormented him for so many years. But the southern
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mountains were very far away.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Theon must have shared something of his mother's powers,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for he said quietly:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "If we started at dawn, we could reach the fortress by
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 nightfall. I've never been there, but I think I could End the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 way."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin thought it over. He was tired, his feet were sore\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 , and the muscles of his thighs were aching with the unaccustomed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 effort. It was very tempting to leave it until another
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 time. Yet there might be no other time, and there was even. the possibility that the actinic explosion had been a signal
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for help.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Bene\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ath the dim light of the failing stars, Alvin wrestled
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 65
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 with his thoughts and presently made his decision. Nothing
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had changed: the mountains resumed their watch over the sleeping land. But a turning-point in history had come a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 nd
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 gone, and the human race was moving towards a strange
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 new future.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The sun had just lifted above the eastern wall of Lys when
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 they reached the outskirts of the forest. Here, nature had
