\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the choice that might soon lie before him. Until now he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had almos\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t forgotten it. He had believed that, somehow,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Council would resolve the difficulty. Now he realized
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that its decision might not be to his liking.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The voice of Seranis was troubled when she began to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 speak, and from her occasional pauses Alvin could tel\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 l that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 she was repeating words already rehearsed.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Alvin," she began, "there are many things I did not tell
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 you before, but which you must learn now if you are to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 understand our actions.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "You know one of the reasons for the isolation of our
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 81
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 82 AGAINST \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 two races. The fear of the Invaders, that dark shadow in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the depths of every human mind, turned your people against
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the world and made them lose themselves in their own
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 dreams. Here in Lys that fear has never been so great,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 although we bo\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 re the burden of the attack. We had a better
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 reason for our actions, and what we did, we did with open
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 eyes.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Long ago, Alvin, men sought immortality and at last
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 achieved it. They forgot that a world which had banished
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 death must also banish birth. The power to extend his life
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 inde6nitely brought contentment to the individual but stagnation
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to the race. You once told me that you were the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 only child to be born in Diaspar for seven thousand years--
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 but you have seen how ma\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ny children we have here in Airlee.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Ages ago we sacriEced our immortality, but Diaspar still
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 follows the false dream. That is why our ways parted--and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 why they must never meet again."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Although the words had been more than half expected,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the blow seemed non\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 e the less for its anticipation. Yet Alvin refused to admit the failure of all his plans--half-formed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 though they were--and only part of his brain was listening
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to Seranis now. He understood and noted all her words, but
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the conscious portion of his mind wa\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 s retracing the road to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Diaspar, trying to imagine every obstacle that could be placed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 in his way.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Seranis was clearly unhappy. Her voice was almost pleading
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as it spoke, and Alvin knew that she was talking not only
