\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin walked to the machine and examined the panel
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 above which the light was blinking. Set in it was a window
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of some almost invisible substance, supporting a stylus which
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 passed vertically through it\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 . The point of tlie stylus rested
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 on a sheet of white material which already bore several
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 signatures and dates. The last of them was almost fifty
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thousand years ago, and Alvin recognized the name as that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of a recent President of the Council. Above it only \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 two
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 other names were visible, neither of which meant anything
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to him or to Rorden. Nor was this very surprising, for they
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had been written twenty-three and fifty-seven million years
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 before.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin could see no purpose for this ritual, but he knew
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that he co\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 uld never fathom the workings of the minds that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had built this place. With a slight feeling of unreality he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 grasped the stylus and began to write his name. The instrument
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 seemed completely free to move in the horizontal
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 plane, for in that direction the window offered no more
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 resistance than the wall of a sap-bubble. Yet his full strength
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was incapable of moving it vertically: he knew, because he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 tried.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Carefully he wrote the date and released the stylus. It
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 moved slowly b\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ack across the sheet to its original position
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 --and the panel with its winking light was gone.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 As Alvin walked awav, he wondered why his predecessors
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had come here and what they had sought from the machine.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 No doubt, thousands or millions of years in the f\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 uture, other
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 men would look into that panel and ask themselves: "Who
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was Alvin of Loronei?" Or would they? Perhaps they would
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 exclaim instead: "Look! Here's Alvin's signature!"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The thought was not untypical of him in his present
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mood, but he knew better th\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 an to share it with his friend.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 At the entrance to the corridor they looked back across
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the cave, and the illusion was stronger than ever. Lying
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 beneath them was a dead city of strange white buildings,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 a city bleached by the fierce light not meant for huma\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 n
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 eyes. Dead it might be, for it had never lived, but Alvin
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 knew that when Diaspar had passed away these machines
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would still be here, never turning their minds from the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thoughts greater men than he had given them long ago.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 They spoke little on the way bac\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 k through the streets
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of Diaspar, streets bathed with sunlight which seemed pale
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF Night 99
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and wan after the glare of the machine city. Each in his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 own way was thinking of the knowledge that would soon
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 be his, and neither had any regard for the beauty of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 great towers drifting past, or the curious glances of their
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 fellow citizens.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was strange, thought Alvin, how everything that had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 happened to him led up to this moment. He knew well
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 enough that men\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  were makers of their own destinies, yet
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 since he had met Rorden events seemed to have moved
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 automatically towards a predetermined goal. Alaine's message--Lys--Shalmirane--at
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 every stage he might have turned
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 aside with unseeing eyes, but something had led \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 him on
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was pleasant to pretend that Fate had favoured him, but
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his rational mind knew better. Any man might have found
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the path his footsteps had traced, and countless times in the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 past ages others must have gone almost as far. He was simply
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the first t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 o be lucky.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The first to be luclcy. The words echoed mockingly in his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ears as they stepped through the door of Rorden's chamber.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Quietly waiting for them, with hands folded patiently across
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his lap, was a man wearing a curious garb unlike any that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin ha\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 d ever seen before. He glanced enquiringly at Rorden,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and was instantly shocked by the pallor of his friend's face.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Then he knew who the visitor was.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He rose as they entered and made a stiff, formal bow.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Without a word he handed a small cylinder to Rorden,\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  who
