\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "It seems that the Council would like a word with us,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin. I'm afraid we've kept it waiting."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin had guessed \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as much. The crisis had come sooner
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 --much sooner--than he had expected. He was not, he told
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 himself, afraid of the Council, but the interruption was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 maddening. His eyes strayed involuntarily to the robots.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "You'll have to leave them behind," said Rorden f\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 irmly.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Their eyes met and clashed. Then Alvin glanced at the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Messenger.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Very well," he said quietly.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The party was very silent on its way to the Council
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Chamber. Alvin was marshalling the arguments he had never
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 100 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 properly thou\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ght out, believing they would not be needed for
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 many years. He was far more annoyed than alarmed, and he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 felt angry at himself for being so unprepared.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 They waited only a few minutes in the anteroom, but it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was long enough for, Alvin to wonder why, if he w\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as unafraid, his legs felt so curiously weak. Then the great doors contracted,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and they walked towards the twenty men gathered
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 round their famous table.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 This, Alvin knew, was the first Council Meeting in his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 lifetime, and he felt a little flattered as he n\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 oticed that there
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were no empty seats. He had never known that Jeserac was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 a Council member. At his startled gaze the old man shifted
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 uneasily in his chair and gave him a furtive smile as if to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 say: "This is nothing to do with me." Most of the other
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 faces Alvin had expected, and only two were quite unknown
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to him.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The President began to address them in a friendly voice, and looking at the familiar faces before him, Alvin could
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 see no great cause for Rorden's alarm. His confidence began
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to return: Rord\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 en, he decided, was something of a coward.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 In that he did his friend less than justice, for although courage
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had never been one of Rorden's most conspicuous qualities,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his worry concerned his ancient office almost as much as
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 himself. Never in history had a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  Keeper of the Records been
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 relieved of his position: Rorden was very anxious not to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 create a precedent.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 In the few minutes since he had entered the Council
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Chamber, Alvin's plans had undergone a remarkable change.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The speech he had so carefully rehearsed \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was forgotten: the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Ene phrases he had been practising were reluctantly discarded.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 To his support now had come his most treacherous ally--
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that sense of the ridiculous which had always made it impossible
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for him to take very seriously even the most solemn
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 o\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ccasions. The Council might meet once in a thousand years:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 it might control the destinies of Diaspar--but those who sat
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 upon it were only tired old men. Alvin knew Jeserac, and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he did not believe that the others would be very different.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He felt a disconcer\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ting pity for them, and suddenly remembered
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the words Seranis had spoken to him in Lys: "Ages
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ago we sacrificed our immortality, but Diaspar still follows
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the false dream." That in truth these men had done, and he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 did not believe it had brought them happiness.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 So when at.the President's invitation Alvin began to describe
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his journey to Lys, he was to all appearances no more
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 than a boy who had by chance stumbled on a discovery
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 101
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he though\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t of little importance. There was no hint of any
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 plan or deeper purpose: only natural curiosity had led him
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 out of Diaspar. It might have happened to anyone, yet he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 contrived to give the impression that he expected a little
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 praise for his cleverness. Of Sh\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 almirane and the robots, he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 said nothing at all.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was quite a good performance, though Alvin was the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 only person who could fully appreciate it. The Council as a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 whole seemed favourably impressed, but Jeserac wore an
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 expression in which relief struggled w\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ith incredulity. At
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden, Alvin dared not look.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 When he had quite finished, there was a brief silence while
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Council considered his statement. Then the President
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 spoke again:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "We fully appreciate," he said, choosing his words with
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 obvious care, "that \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 you had the best of motives in what you
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 did. However, you have created a somewhat difficult situation
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for us. Are you quite sure that your discovery was accidental,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and that no one, shall we say, Influenced you in any way?"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 His eyes wandered thoughtfully t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 owards Rorden.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 For the last time, Alvin yielded to the mischievous prompt-
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ings of his mind.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I wouldn't say that," he replied, after an appearance of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 considerable thought. There was a sudden quickening of interest
