\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that by 'events' he meant Alvin, but there were no comments.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "It's futile to bicker about the past: Diaspar and Lys have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 both made mistakes. When Alvin returns, you may prevent
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 him leaving Earth again--if you can. I don't \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 think you will
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 succeed, for he may have leamt a great deal by then. But if
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 what you fear has happened, there's nothing any of us can do
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 139
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 140 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 about it. Earth is helpless--as she has been for millions of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 centuries."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden paused and glanced along the table. His words had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 pleased no one, nor had he expected them to do so.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Yet I don't see why we should be so alarmed. Earth is in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 no greater danger now than she has always been. Why should
