\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 intelligence is less than that of a hu\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 man being"--she smiled
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 a little wryly--"though his thought processes are much faster and he learns very quickly. He also has some powers we dp
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 not yet understand. The whole of the past seems open to his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mind, in a way that's difficult to "describe. He must\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  have used
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that ability to follow your path back to Earth."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin stood in silence, for once somewhat overcome. He
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 realized how right Theon had been to bring Vanamonde to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Lys. And he knew how lucky he had been ever to outwit
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Seranis: that was not something\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  he would do twice in a lifetime.
\par 
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Do you mean," he asked, "that Vanamonde has only just
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 been born?"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "By his standards, yes. His actual age is very great, though
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 apparently less than Man's. The extraordinary thing is that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he insists that we created him, a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 nd there's no doubt that his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 origin is bound up with all the great mysteries of the past."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "What's happening to Vanamonde now?" asked Theon
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 in a slightly possessive voice.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The historians of Grevam are questioning him. They are
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 trying to map out the main o\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 utlines of the past, but the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 work will take years. Vanamonde can describe the past in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 perfect detail, but as he doesn't understand what he sees it's
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 very difficult to work with him."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin wondered how Seranis knew all this: then he realized
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that probably every waking mind in Lys was watching the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 progress of the great research.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Rorden should be here," he said, coming to a sudden
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 decision. "I'm going to Diaspar to fetch him."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "And Jeserac," he added, in a determined afterthought.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden had ne\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ver seen a whirlwind, but if one had hit
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 him the experience would have felt perfectly familiar. There
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were times when his sense of reality ceased to function, and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the feeling that everything was a dream became almost overwhelming.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 This was such a moment no\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 w.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He closed his eyes and tried to recall the familiar room in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Diaspar which had once been both a part of his personality
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and a barrier against the outer world. What would he have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thought, he wondered, could he have looked into the future
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 when he had 6rst \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 met Alvin and seen the outcome of that
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 147
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 encounter? But of one thing he was sure and a little proud
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he would not have turned aside.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The boat was moving slowly across the lake with a gentle
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 rocking motion that Rorden found rathe\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 r pleasant. Why the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 village of Grevam had been built on an island he could not
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 imagine: it seemed a most inconvenient arrangement. It was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 true that the colored houses, which seemed to float at anchor
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 upon the tiny waves, made a scene of almost unreal beaut\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 y
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 That was all very well, thought Rorden, but one couldn't
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 spend the whole of one's life staring at scenery. Then he remembered
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that this was precisely what many of these eccentric
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 people did.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Eccentric or not, they had minds he could respect. To
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 him the thoughts of Vanamonde were as meaningless as a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thousand voices shouting together in some vast, echoing cave.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Yet the men of Lys could disentangle them, could record
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 them to be analyzed at leisure. Already the structure of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 past, which had once s\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 eemed lost forever, was becoming
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 faintly visible. And it was so strange and unexpected that it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 appeared to bear no resemblance at all to the history that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden had always believed.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 In a few months he would present his first report to Diaspar.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Though its c\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ontents were still uncertain, he knew that it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would end forever the sterile isolation of his race. The barriers
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 between Lys and Diaspar would vanish when their origin was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 understood, and the mingling of the two great cultures would
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 invigorate mankind for a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ges to come. Yet even this now
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 seemed no more than a minor by-product of the great research
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that was just beginning. If what Vanamonde had hinted was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 indeed true, Man's horizons must soon embrace not merely
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Earth, but must enfold the stars and reach ou\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t to the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Galaxies beyond. But of these further vistas it was still too
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 early to be sure.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Calitrax, chief historian of Lys, met them at the little
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 jetty. He was a tall, slightly stooping man and Rorden wondered
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 how, without the help of the Masters Associato\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 rs, he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had ever managed to learn so much in his short life. It did
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 not occur to him that the very absence of such machines was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the reason for the wonderful memories he had met in Crevam.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 They walked together beside one of the innumerable canals
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that made life in the village so hazardous to strangers. Calitrax
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 seemed a little preoccupied, and Rorden knew that part of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his mind was still with Vanamonde.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Have you settled your date-fixing procedure yet?" asked
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden presently, feeling somewhat negle\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 cted.
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 148 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Calitrax remembered his duties as host and broke contact
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 with obvious reluctance.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Yes," he said. "It had to be the astronomical method. We
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 think it's accurate to ten thousand years even back to the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Dawn Ages. It could \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 be even better, but that's good enough
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to mark out the main epochs."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "What about the Invaders? Has Bensor located them?"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "No: he made one attempt but it's hopeless to look for
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 any isolated period. What we're doing now is to go back to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the beginning of hist\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ory and then take cross-sections at regular
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 intervals. We'll link them together by guesswork until we
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 can fill in the details. If only Vanamonde could interpret
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 what he sees! As it is we have to work through masses of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 irrelevant material."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I wonder what h\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 e thinks about the whole affair: it must
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 all be rather puzzling to him."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Yes, I suppose it must. But he's very docile and friendly,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and I think he's happy, if one can use that word. So Theon
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 believes, and they seem to have a curious sort of affinity. Ah,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 here's Bensor with the latest ten million years of history. I'll leave you in his hands."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 THE COUNCIL CHAMBER HAD ALTERED LITTLE SINCE ALVIN'S
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 last visit, for the seldom-used projection equipment was so
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 inconspicuous that one could easily have overlooked i\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t. There
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were two empty chairs along the great table: one, he knew,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was Jeserac's. But though he was in Lys, Jeserac would be
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 watching this meeting, as would almost all the world.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 If Rorden recalled their last appearance in this room, he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 did not care to me\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ntion it. But the councillors certainly remembered,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as Alvin could tell by the ambiguous glances he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 received. He wondered what they would be thinking when
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 they had heard Rorden's story. Already, in a few months, the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Present had changed out of all recogniti\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 on--and now they
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were going to lose the Past.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden began to speak. The great ways of Diaspar would
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 be empty of traffic: the city would be hushed as Alvin had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 known it only once before in his life. It was waiting, waiting
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for the veil of the past to be li\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 fted again after--if Calitrax
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was right--more than fifteen hundred million years.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Very briefly, Rordan ran through the accepted history of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the race--the history that both Diaspar and Lys had always
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 believed beyond question. He spoke of the unknown peoples
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of the Dawn Civilizations, who had left behind them nothing
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 149
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 but a handful of great names and the fading legends of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Empire. Even at the beginning, so the story went, Man had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 desired the stars and at lart attained them. For\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  millions of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 years he had expanded across the Galaxy, gathering system
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 after system beneath his sway. Then, out of the darkness
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 beyond the rim of the Universe, the Invaders had struck and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 wrenched from him all that he had won.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The retreat to the Solar System had been bitter and must
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have lasted many ages. Earth itself was barely saved by the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 fabulous battles that raged round Shalmirane. When all was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 over, Man was left with only his memories and the world on
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 which he had been bor\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 n.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden paused: he looked round the great room and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 smiled slightly as his eyes met Alvin's.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "So much for the tales we have believed since our records
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 began. I must tell you now that they are false--false in every
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 detail--so false that even now we have no\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t fully reconciled them with the truth."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He waited for the full meaning of his words to strike
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 home. Then, speaking slowly and carefully, but after the Erst
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 few minutes never consulting his notes, he gave the city the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 knowledge that had been won from the m\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ind of Vanamonde.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was not even true that Man had reached the stars. The
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 whole of his little empire was bounded by the orbit of Perse-
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 phone, for interstellar space proved a barrier beyond his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 power to cross. His entire civilization was huddled round the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 sun, and was still very young when--the stars reached him.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The impact must have been shattering. Despite his failures,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Man had never doubted that one day he would conquer the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 deeps of space. He believed too that if the Universe held his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 equals, it did not\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  hold his peers. Now he knew that both
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 beliefs were wrong, and that out among the stars were minds
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 far greater than his own. For many centuries, first in the ships
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of other races and later in machines built with borrowed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 knowledge, Man had \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 explored the Galaxy. Everywhere he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 found cultures he could understand but could not match, and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 here and there he encountered minds which would soon have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 passed altogether beyond his comprehension.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The shock was tremendous, but it proved the making of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the r\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ace. Sadder and infinitely wiser, Man had returned to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Solar System to brood upon the knowledge he had gained.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He would accept the challenge and slowly he evolved a plan
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 which gave hope for the future.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Once the physical sciences had been Man's greatest \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 interest.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Now he turned even more fiercely to genetics and the
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 150 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 study of the mind. Whatever the cost, he would drive himself
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to the limits of his evolution.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The great experiment had consumed the entire energies
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of the race for\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  millions of years. All that striving, all that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 sacri5ce and toil, became only a handful of words in Rorden's
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 narrative. It had brought Man his greatest victories. He had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 banished disease: he could live forever if he wished, and in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mastering telepathy he h\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ad bent the most subtle of all powers
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to his will.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 He was ready to go out again, relying upon his own resources,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 into the great spaces of the Galaxy. He would meet
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as an equal the races of the worlds from which he had once
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 turned aside. And he would play h\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 is full part in the story of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Universe.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 These things he did. From this age, perhaps the most
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 spacious in off history, came the legends of the Empire. It
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had been an Empire of many races, but this had been forgotten
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 in the drama, too tremendous for tragedy, in which it had come to its end.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The Empire had lasted for at least a billion years. It must
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have known many crises, perhaps even wars, but all these
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were lost in the sweep of great races moving together towards
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ma\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 turity.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "We can be proud," continued Rorden, "of the part our
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ancestors played in this story. Even when they had reached
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 their cultural plateau, they lost none of their initiative. We
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 deal now with conjecture rather than proven fact, but it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 seems certain t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 hat the experiments which were at once the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Empire's downfall and its crowning glory were inspired and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 directed by Man.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The philosophy underlying these experiments appears to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have been this. Contact with other species had shown Man
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 how profoundly a race's \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 world-picture depended upon its
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 physical body and the sense organs with which it was equipped.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was argued that a true picture of the Universe could be
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 attained, if at all, only by a mind which was free from such
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 physical limitations--a pure mentality, i\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 n fact. This idea was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 common among most very ancient religions and was believed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 by many to be the goal of evolution.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Largely as a result of the experience gained in his own
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 regeneration, Man suggested that the creation of such beings
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 should be attempted. \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was the greatest challenge ever thrown
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 out to intelligence in the Universe, and after centuries of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 debate it was accepted. All the races of the Galaxy joined
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 together in its fulfilment.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Half a billion years were to separate the dream from the
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF Night l5(
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 reality. Civilizations were to rise and fall, again and yet again
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the age-long toil of worlds was to be lost, but the goal was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 never forgotten. One day we may know the full story of this,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the greatest sustained effort in all h\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 istory. Today we only
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 know that its ending was a disaster that almost wrecked the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Galaxy.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Into this period Vanamonde's mind refuses to go. There
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 is a narrow region of time which is blocked to him; but only,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 we believe, by his own fears. At its beginning w\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 e can see the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Empire at the summit of its glory, taut with the expectation
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of coming success. At its end, only a few thousand years later,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Empire is shattered and the stars themselves are dimmed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as though drained of their power. Over the Galaxy hangs a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 pall of fear, a fear with which is linked the name: The Mad
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Mind.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "What must have happened in that short period is not
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 hard to guess. The pure mentality had been created, but it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was either insane or, as seems more likely from other sources,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was implacably\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  hostile to matter. For centuries it ravaged the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Universe until brought under control by forces of which we
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 cannot guess. Whatever weapon the Empire used in its extremity
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 squandered the resources of the stars: from the memories
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of that conflict spring some\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 , though not all, of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 legends of the Invaders. But of this I shall presently say more.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The Mad Mind could not be destroyed, for it was immortal.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 It was driven to the edge of the Galaxy and there
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 imprisoned in a way we do not understand. Its prison was a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 strange artificial star known as the Black Sun, and there it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 remains to this day. When the Black Sun dies, it will be free
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 again. How far in the future that day lies there is no way of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 telling."
\par \page 
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ALVIN GLANCED QUICKLY AROUND THE GREAT ROOM, WHICH
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had become utterly silent. The councillors, for the most part,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 sat rigid in their seats, staring at Rorden with a trancelike
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 immobility. Even to Alvin, who had already heard the story
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 in fragments, Rorden\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 's narrative still had the excitement of r
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 a newly unfolding drama. To the councillors, the impact of | his revelations must be overwhelming.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden was speaking again in a quiet, more subdued voice
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 as he described the last days of the Empire. This was the\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  age,
