\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of disaster.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Though the Galaxy had been laid waste by the Mad Mind,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the re\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 sources of the Empire were still enormous, and its
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 spirit was unbroken. With a courage at which we can only
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 marvel, the great experiment was resumed and a search made
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for the flaw that had caused the catastrophe. There were
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 now, of course, many who opposed\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  the work and predicted
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 further disasters, but they were overruled. The project went
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ahead and, with the knowledge so bitterly gained, this time I
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 it succeeded.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The new race that was born had a potential intellect that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 could not even be measured. But it was completely infantile:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 we do not know if this was expected by its creators, but it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 seems likely that they knew it to be inevitable. Millions of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 years would be needed before it reached maturity, and nothing
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 could be don\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 e to hasten the process. Vanamonde was the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 first of these minds: there must be others elsewhere in the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 154
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 155
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Galaxy, but we believe that only a very few were created, for Vanamonde has never encountered any of his fellows.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  creation of the pure mentalities was the greatest
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 achievement of Galactic civilization: in it Man played a
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 major and perhaps a dominant part. I have made no reference
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to Earth itself, for its story is too small a thread to
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 be traced in the great tapestry.\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  Since it had always been
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 drained of its most adventurous spirits our planet had inevitably
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 become somewhat conservative, and in the end it opposed
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the scientists who created Vanamonde. Certainly it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 played no part at all in the Enal act.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The work of the E\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 mpire was now finished: the men of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that age looked round at the stars they had ravaged in their
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 desperate peril, and they made the decision that might have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 been expected. They would leave the Universe to Vanamonde.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "The choice was not hard to make, for the\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  Empire had
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 now made the first contacts with a very great and very strange
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 civilization far around the curve of the cosmos. This civilization,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 if the hints we can gather are correct, had evolved on
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the purely physical plane further than had been believed possible.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 There were, it seemed, more solutions than one to the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 problem of ultimate intelligence. But this we can only guess:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 all we know for certain is that within a very short period of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 time our an\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 cestors and their fellow races have gone upon a journey which we cannot follow. Vanamonde's thoughts seem
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 bounded by the confines of the Galaxy, but through his mind
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 we have watched the beginning of that great adventure--"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 A PALE WRAITH OF ITS FORMER CLORY\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 , THE SLOWLY TURNING
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 wheel of the Galaxy hangs in nothingness. Throughout its
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 length are the great empty rents which the Mad Mind has
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 torn--wounds that in ages to come the drifting stars will fill.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 But they wiJI never restore the splendor that has gone.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Ma\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 n is about to leave his Universe, as once he left his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 world. And not only Man, but the thousand other races that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have worked with him to make the Empire. They have gathered
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 together, here at the edge of the Galaxy, with its whole
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thickness between them and\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  the goal they will not reach
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 for ages.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The long line of fire strikes across the Universe, leaping
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 from star to star. In a moment of time a thousand suns
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have died, feeding their energies to the dim and monstrous
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 shape that has torn along the axis of the G\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 alaxy and is now
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 receding into the abyss. .. .
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 156 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "THE EMPIRE HAD NOW LEFT THE UNIVERSE, TO MEET ITS
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 destiny elsewhere. When its heirs, the pure mentalities, have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 reached their full stature we believe it will return again. But
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 hat day must still lie far ahead.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "This, in its outlines, is the story of Galactic civilization.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Our own history, which we thought so important, is no more
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 than a belated episode which we have not yet examined in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 detail. But it seems that many of the older, less adventurous
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 races refused to leave their homes. Our direct ancestors were
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 among them. Most of these races fell into decadence and are
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 now extinct: our own world barely escaped the same fate. In
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Transiti\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 on Centuries--which really lasted for millions of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 years--the knowledge of the past was lost or else deliberately
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 destroyed. The latter seems more probable: we believe that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Man sank into a superstitious barbarism during which he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 distorted history to remove \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 his sense of impotence and failure.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The legend of the Invaders is certainly false, and the Battle
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of Shalmirane is a myth. True, Shalmirane exists, and was one
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of the greatest weapons ever forged--but it was used against
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 no intelligent enemy. Once the Eart\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 h had a single giant
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 satellite, the Moon. When it began to fall, Shalmirane was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was built to destroy it. Around that destruction have been
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 weaved the legends you all know, and there are many such."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Rorden paused, and smiled a little ruefully.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "There are ot\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 her paradoxes that have not yet been resolved,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 but the problem is one for the psychologist rather
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 than the historian. Even my records cannot be wholly trusted,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and bear clear evidence of tampering in the very remote past.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Only Diaspar and Lys survived the\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  period of decadence--
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Diaspar thanks to the perfection of its machines, Lys owing
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to its partial isolation and the unusual intellectual powers of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 its people. But both cultures, even when they had struggled
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 back to their former level, were distorted by the fears and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 myths they had inherited.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "Those fears need haunt us no longer. All down the ages,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 we have now discovered, there were men who rebelled against
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 them and maintained a tenuous link between Diaspar an\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 d
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Lys. Now the last barriers can be swept aside and our two
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 races can move together into the Future--whatever it may
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 bring."
