\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 They were now moving up the slope to the Tomb, through
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the long avenue of eternal trees. At its end, the a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 venue was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 blocked by Alvin's ship, looking strangely out of place in
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 these familiar surroundings.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "There," said Rorden suddenly, "is the greatest mystery of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 all. Who was the Master? Where did he get this ship and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the three robots?"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I've been thinking abou\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 t that," answered Theon. "We
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 know that he came from the Seven Suns, and there might
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 have been a fairly high culture there when civilization on
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Earth was at its lowest. The ship itself is obviously the work
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of the Empire.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I believe that the Master was esca\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ping from his own
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 people. Perhaps he had ideas with which they didn't agree:
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he was a philosopher, and a rather remarkable one. He found
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 our ancestors friendly but superstitious and tried to educate
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 them, but they misunderstood and distorted his teachings.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The Great Ones were no more than the men of the Empire
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 --only it wasn't Earth they had left, but the Universe itself.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The Master's disciples didn't understand or didn't believe
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 this, and all their mythology and ritual was founded on that
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 158 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 false premise. One day I intend to go into the Master's history
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 and find why he tried to conceal his past. I think it will
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 be a very interesting story."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "We've a good deal to thank him for," said Rorden as
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 they entered the shi\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 p. "Without him we would never have
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 learned the truth about the past."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I'm not so sure," said Alvin. "Sooner or later Vanamonde
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would have discovered us. And I believe there may be other
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ships hidden on Earth: one day I mean to find them."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 The city was no\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 w too distant to be recognized as the work
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of man, and the curve of the planet was becoming visible. In
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 a little while they could see the line of twilight, thousands
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of miles away on its never-ending march across the desert.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Above and around were the stars\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 , still brilliant for all the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 glory they had lost.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 For a long time Rorden stared at the desolate panorama
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he had never seen before. He felt a sudden contemptuous
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 anger for the men of the past who had let Earth's beauty
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 die through their own neglect. If one\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  of Alvin's dreams came
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 true, and the great transmutation plants still existed, it
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would not be many centuries before the oceans rolled again.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 There was so much to do in the years ahead. Rorden knew
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that he stood between two ages: around him he could feel
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the pulse of mankind beginning to quicken again. There
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 were great problems to be faced, and Diaspar would face
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 them. The recharting of the past would take centuries, but
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 when it was finished Man would have recovered all that he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 had lost. And always now in the background would be the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 great enigma of Vanamonde--
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 If Calitrax was right, Vanamonde had already evolved
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 more swiftly than his creators had expected, and the philosophers
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 of Lys had great hopes of future co-operation which t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 hey
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would confide to no one. They had become very attached
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 to the childlike supermind, and perhaps they believed that
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 they could foreshorten the eons which his natural evolution
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 would require. But Rorden knew that the ultimate destiny of
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Vanamonde was some\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 thing in which Man would play no
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 part. He had dreamed, and he believed the dream was true,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 that at the end of the Universe Vanamonde and the Mad
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Mind must meet each other among the corpses of the stars.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin broke into his reverie and Rorden turned from t\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 screen.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I wanted you to see this," said Alvin quietly. "It may be
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 many centuries before you have another chance."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "You're not leaving Earth?"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "No: even if there are other civilizations in this Galaxy, I
\par \page \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 AGAINST THE FALL OF NIGHT 159
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 doubt if they'd be\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39  worth the trouble of finding. And there
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 is so much to do here--"
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin looked down at the great deserts, but his eyes saw
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 instead the waters that would be sweeping over them a thousand
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 years from now. Man had rediscovered his world, and
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he would make it b\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 eautiful while he remained upon it. And
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 after that--
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 "I am going to send this ship out of the Galaxy, to follow
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the Empire wherever it has gone. The search may take ages,
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 but the robot will never tire. One day our cousins will receive
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 my message, and they'll know that we are waiting for them
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 here on Earth. They will return, and I hope that by then
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 we'll be worthy of them, however great they have become."
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Alvin fell silent, staring into the future he had shaped but
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 which he might never s\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 ee. While Man was rebuilding his
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 world, this ship would be crossing the darkness between the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 galaxies, and in thousands of years to come it would return.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 Perhaps he would be there to meet it, but if not, he was
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 well content.
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 They were now above the Pole, a\hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 nd the planet beneath
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 them was an almost perfect hemisphere. Looking down upon
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 the belt of twilight, Alvin realized that he was seeing at one
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 instant both sunrise and sunset on opposite sides of the
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 world. The symbolism was so perfect and so striking that \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 he
\par \hich\af39\dbch\af31505\loch\f39 was to remember this moment all his life.
